{"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","roleHeading":"Article"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Authentication-Flow","text":"Authentication Flow"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the changes being made:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is no longer stored inside of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": now, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","isActive":true}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","text":"`SessionConfiguration`","level":2,"anchor":"SessionConfiguration"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned previously, ","type":"text"},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8"},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":" have been made: ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/getSession()":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","title":"getSession()","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/getsession()","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getSession","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() "},{"text":"async","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}]},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/authenticate(with:password:)":{"title":"authenticate(with:password:)","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProt